2. Use Terminal to Ignore Specific Updates:
You can use the Terminal to ignore a specific update. This requires knowing the exact identifier for the update you want to avoid. Hereâ€™s how:

Open Terminal:

Go to Applications > Utilities > Terminal.
List Available Updates:

Type the following command and press Enter:
softwareupdate --list

Ignore the Specific Update:
sudo softwareupdate --ignore "updateIdentifier"
For example:
sudo softwareupdate --ignore "macOS 13.4.1 Update"

3. Reverting the Ignored Update:
If you later decide that you want to allow the previously ignored update, you can remove it from the ignore list.

Unignore All Updates:
sudo softwareupdate --reset-ignored
